	<LO name="Learning Object">
		<IFC helpfile="FileLocation + 'help.htm'" name="Interface" title="My Learning Object" visuals="1">
			<PG name="[Untitled]" title="Page Title" help="Page Help">
				<DIS name="textDisplay" x="447" y="35" w="307" h="396" type="text"><![CDATA[The Language selection is dynamic based on the contents of language-config.xml.

Selecting a language loads the file, which sets engine.currentLanguage. You could use that to display different languages in your content from templateData easily.

The page refreshes when a language is loaded, just as it does when changing themes etc.

It should cover all interface items and text to speech.

Things you are interested in:

engine.currentLanguage:String //the current language
rootIcon.loadLanguage(file):void //loads a new file

engine.languageData //the xml.toObject() of the language xml file
engine.languageConfig //the xml.toObject() of the language-config file


]]></DIS>
				<DIS name="currentLanguage" x="20" y="112" w="400" h="18" type="text"><![CDATA[{'Current Language:' + engine.currentLanguage}]]></DIS>
				<SCR name="makeLanguageList"><![CDATA[if (icon.built != 'true'){
  icon.nextSibling.firstChild.duplicate(languageConfig.languages[0].language.length - 1);
  icon.built = 'true';
}


]]></SCR>
				<INT name="selectLanguage" perpetual="0">
					<RES name="protoSelect" type="button" x="20" y="icon.index() == 0 ? 20 : _ytile + 10" label="{languageConfig.languages[0].language[icon.index()].name}" erase="1" exit="0">
						<SCR name="[Untitled]"><![CDATA[rootIcon.loadLanguage('languages/' + languageConfig.languages[0].language[icon.parentNode.index()].file);]]></SCR>
					</RES>
				</INT>
			</PG>
			<PG name="[Untitled]" title="Page Title" help="Page Help">
				<DIS name="[Untitled]" x="0" y="0" w="400" h="10" type="text"><![CDATA[just another page]]></DIS>
			</PG>
		</IFC>
		<BIN name="Deleted Items" />
	</LO>

